# 副簽  
(pos:名詞)  
<explanation>  
yue:文件、證件或合約上，跟住正簽名（主簽）之後簽署嘅簽名（通常由副職、代理人或協辦人員簽署）；量詞一般唔用，但可說「一紙副簽」  
eng:counter-signature; secondary signature (on a document, following the primary signature)  

<eg>  
yue:呢份合約要正簽同副簽都簽咗先至生效。 (ni1 fan3 hap6 jyu6 jiu3 zing3 sin3 tung4 fu3 sin3 dou1 cin3 zo2 sin1 zi3 siu3 zyu6.)  
eng:This contract only becomes effective once both the primary and counter-signatures are affixed.  

yue:呢張申請表要老細同副簽一齊簽名。 (ni1 zoeng1 san2 cin1 biu2 jiu3 lou5 zai3 tung4 fu3 sin3 jat1 chi2 cin3 sin3.)  
eng:This application form requires both the boss’s and the counter-signatory’s signatures. [end of text]


